@Thork Rynu > "I'm sure women prefer a man-child as a husband than a wife-beater but wouldn't it be great if women could have men for husbands?"

As I pointed out before we don't know their disposition. A collector of toys could be more emotionally stable than you. To not get your paranoia up I'll say they could be more emotionally stable than me. I'm not a collector of toys. So I fit the criteria too. They cannot be automatically a "man-child" because they collect toys. That is a spurious claim you're making. You're mixing "toys", and "man", and calling it based on some normative view you have of toys. But that's not how it works. Toys mixed with man has not been demonstrated to be any different than not toys mixed with man. In fact I've met men who are very childish who are adamantly against such toy collection. So not toys mixed with man didn't appear to help them.

Also when did women come into this? Are you here to save women from men who collect toys? I bet you didn't know people gravitate towards people who have similar interests. And some women collect toys too. You fell on your own sword.

